1
00:00:04,782 --> 00:00:06,873
When people conceive of God, 
they think

2
00:00:06,873 --> 00:00:11,741
the highest conception of God 
generally is the Creator,

3
00:00:11,741 --> 00:00:14,039
who created the world 
and the universes.

4
00:00:14,070 --> 00:00:16,297
Always “Creator”, “Creator”.

5
00:00:16,574 --> 00:00:18,848
[Beyond The Creator]

6
00:00:19,341 --> 00:00:22,987
And we had this discussion in China,

7
00:00:22,987 --> 00:00:25,957
how, in Kṛṣṇa conception,

8
00:00:25,957 --> 00:00:30,890
creation is a secondary function.

9
00:00:30,890 --> 00:00:33,870
Kṛṣṇa is not directly involved in creation.

10
00:00:33,870 --> 00:00:36,607
What is He doing? Play.

11
00:00:36,607 --> 00:00:41,032
Deva-mayī.
You know what deva means?

12
00:00:41,032 --> 00:00:44,785
The general word for deva means god.

13
00:00:44,785 --> 00:00:47,450
Deva, devi: god, goddess.

14
00:00:47,450 --> 00:00:50,393
But not when applied to Kṛṣṇa;

15
00:00:50,393 --> 00:00:52,714
what deva means is ‘playful’,

16
00:00:52,714 --> 00:00:59,881
and not only playful, but divine love
pastimes—that type of play.

17
00:00:59,881 --> 00:01:01,804
Divine love play.

18
00:01:01,804 --> 00:01:04,448
That’s the one 
who is called Deva.

19
00:01:04,448 --> 00:01:07,079
Deva-mayī 
means Śrīmatiī Rādhārāṇī,

20
00:01:07,079 --> 00:01:10,418
who is supplying 
all the divine love play to Kṛṣṇa.

